The **File List Human Task** displays a configurable list of files in the Workplace task editor. The displayed files can be selected by the Workplace user and used in a subsequent Business Case step. The input XML also allows the Workplace administrator to enable or disable the following user actions:

- Select all

- Multi-select

- Specific files being pre-selected

- File preview

## Interface
![](data:image/png;base64,)File List Human Task in the task editor of Workplace 2

## Configuration
The configuration of a Human Task is done in Process Designer. It consists of three mappings:

- **General parameters:** General properties of the Human Task

- **Input parameters:** Defines the input data which will be consumed by Process Engine

- **Output parameters:** Defines the output data which will be exposed to the user and/or the system

The individual fields for each parameter group are described in detail below.

### General task parameters
All Human Task types require general task parameters. These general parameters are described in [Workplace 2 Human Tasks](https://docs.doxee.com/doxee-platform/docs/workplace-2-6-6-human-tasks-1).

![](data:image/png;base64,)Configuration window for general task parameters in Process Designer

### Input parameters
In addition to the [basic input parameters](https://docs.doxee.com/doxee-platform/docs/workplace-2-6-6-human-tasks-1#basic-input-parameters) common to all Human Task types, the File List Human Task also requires the following type-specific input parameters:

Field

Type

Mandatory or optional

Values

Description

`dataSet`

text/plain

Mandatory

Exactly 1

XML containing the configuration of select and preview actions, as well as the specific files to display.

### Output parameters
In addition to the [basic output parameters](https://docs.doxee.com/doxee-platform/docs/workplace-2-6-6-human-tasks-1#basic-output-parameters) common to all Human Task types, the File List Human Task also requires the following type-specific output parameters:

Field

Type

Values

Description

`dataSet`

text/xml

Exactly 1

XML containing the selected files, in the same format as the input

## Examples
The input XML for the `dataSet` parameter may look like this:

`&lt;data-set&gt;
	&lt;!-- disallow selection of all rows (select all check box) --&gt;
	&lt;select-all-allowed&gt;false&lt;/select-all-allowed&gt;

	&lt;!-- allow multi-selection or not --&gt;
	&lt;multi-select-allowed&gt;true&lt;/multi-select-allowed&gt;

	&lt;!-- source folder with documents --&gt;
	&lt;source-folder&gt;
		&lt;uri&gt;/preview-pdf/&lt;/uri&gt;
		&lt;recursive&gt;true&lt;/recursive&gt;
		&lt;constraints&gt;
			&lt;content-type&gt;
				&lt;name&gt;application/pdf&lt;/name&gt;
				&lt;previewable&gt;true&lt;/previewable&gt;
			&lt;/content-type&gt;
			&lt;content-type&gt;
				&lt;name&gt;image/jpeg&lt;/name&gt;
				&lt;previewable&gt;true&lt;/previewable&gt;
			&lt;/content-type&gt;
			&lt;content-type&gt;
				&lt;name&gt;text/html&lt;/name&gt;
				&lt;previewable&gt;false&lt;/previewable&gt;
			&lt;/content-type&gt;
		&lt;/constraints&gt;
	&lt;/source-folder&gt;

	&lt;!-- ready-made list of documents --&gt;
	&lt;documents&gt;
		&lt;document&gt;
			&lt;name&gt;Standard invoice (pre-selected)&lt;/name&gt;
			&lt;selectable&gt;true&lt;/selectable&gt;
			&lt;selected&gt;true&lt;/selected&gt;
			&lt;previewable&gt;true&lt;/previewable&gt;
			&lt;uri&gt;/preview-pdf/standard_invoice.pdf&lt;/uri&gt;
		&lt;/document&gt;
		&lt;document&gt;
			&lt;name&gt;Modern invoice&lt;/name&gt;
			&lt;selectable&gt;true&lt;/selectable&gt;
			&lt;selected&gt;false&lt;/selected&gt;
			&lt;previewable&gt;true&lt;/previewable&gt;
			&lt;filename&gt;modern_invoice.pdf&lt;/filename&gt;
			&lt;base64Content&gt;PHJvb3Q+PC9yb290Pg==&lt;/base64Content&gt;
		&lt;/document&gt;
		&lt;document&gt;
			&lt;name&gt;Business invoice&lt;/name&gt;
			&lt;selectable&gt;true&lt;/selectable&gt;
			&lt;selected&gt;false&lt;/selected&gt;
			&lt;previewable&gt;true&lt;/previewable&gt;
		&lt;/document&gt;
		&lt;document&gt;
			&lt;name&gt;Simplified invoice (pre-selected and not-selectable)&lt;/name&gt;
			&lt;selectable&gt;false&lt;/selectable&gt;
			&lt;selected&gt;true&lt;/selected&gt;
			&lt;previewable&gt;true&lt;/previewable&gt;
			&lt;uri&gt;/preview-pdf/simplified_invoice.pdf&lt;/uri&gt;
		&lt;/document&gt;
		&lt;document&gt;
			&lt;name&gt;Minimalistic invoice (not-selectable)&lt;/name&gt;
			&lt;selectable&gt;false&lt;/selectable&gt;
			&lt;selected&gt;false&lt;/selected&gt;
			&lt;previewable&gt;false&lt;/previewable&gt;
		&lt;/document&gt;
	&lt;/documents&gt;

&lt;/data-set&gt;`

Process Designer is a GUI tool for creating and testing Infinica Process Definitions (IPD). It&#39;s a support tool for Process Engine, providing a graphical editing and log interface and removing the necessity to manually write XML processes in a text editor.
